    {
      "id": "e6496ef4_e433724a",
      "file_path": "feature-state-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/statemanagement/RepositoryAudit.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "This pattern doesn't match \"repository.audit.id\".\n\nAlso, the advantage of compiling the pattern is you can save the pattern, and reuse it (unlike String.matches). However, this code is compiling the pattern each time through the loop -- why not use a static private variable instead?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 743,
        "name": "Ralph Straubs",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "rs8887@att.com",
        "username": "rs8887"
      },
      "updated": "2019-11-07 16:22:35.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "af3b2f66_12c13424",
      "file_path": "feature-state-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/statemanagement/RepositoryAudit.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "Is it necessary to match \"repository.audit.id\" since it is being treated as the default case and is handled in RepositoryAudit.invoke(...) before handling any additional repositories?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6006,
        "name": "Peyton  Puckett",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "peyton.puckett@att.com",
        "username": "pp5762"
      },
      "updated": "2019-11-07 16:43:00.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e6496ef4_e433724a",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "b48828d1_2949aad6",
      "file_path": "feature-state-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/statemanagement/RepositoryAudit.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "Good point -- as currently coded, index 0 is mandatory, and any other indices are optional.\n\nMaybe index 0 should be optional as well? It could no longer be a special case, except for the property name. That way, they could use 'repository1.' and 'repository2.' to define their repositories, and 'repository.' to define common parameters, such as userids and passwords.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 743,
        "name": "Ralph Straubs",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "rs8887@att.com",
        "username": "rs8887"
      },
      "updated": "2019-11-07 16:57:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "af3b2f66_12c13424",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dd0b86bd_d80a96f0",
      "file_path": "feature-state-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/statemanagement/RepositoryAudit.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "I don't think so.  However, I'd move this Pattern to a static final field.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2019-11-07 17:03:09.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "af3b2f66_12c13424",
      "unresolved": true
    },
